    {
      "id": "ea4dfc88_040d42e5",
      "file_path": "main/pom.xml",
      "patchset_number": 10,
      "line": 73,
      "message": "Checked with Francesco and had a look in clamp. Seems like micrometer version is specified here. Also all spring boot starter components' and versions are specified in the policy-parent. I guess we have more control this way.\nBut, just thinking which one is better. From a managing point of view isn't it better to have dependency management like this and let spring decide on versions of spring components to bring in, and we could still specify the specific version if needed in the policy-parent which should override any spring-boot managed versions.\nThoughts?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4903,
        "name": "Ajith Sreekumar",
        "display_name": "Ajith Sreekumar",
        "email": "ajith.sreekumar@bell.ca",
        "username": "a.sreekumar"
      },
      "updated": "2021-12-13 13:38:33.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "4ee0c1a4_46cc1023",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "7fc502c2_17e3d23f",
      "file_path": "main/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/pap/main/rest/HealthCheckRestControllerV1.java",
      "patchset_number": 10,
      "line": 45,
      "message": "(since spring framework 4.3) You no longer need to specify an explicit injection annotation in such a single-constructor scenario. This is particularly elegant for classes which otherwise do not carry any container annotations at all, for example when programmatically registered (https://spring.io/blog/2016/03/04/core-container-refinements-in-spring-framework-4-3).\nOther suggestion: @RequiredArgsConstructor lombock annotation:\n\n@RestController\n@RequestMapping(path = \"/policy/pap/v1\")\n@RequiredArgsConstructor\npublic class HealthCheckRestControllerV1  extends PapRestControllerV1 {\n\n    private final HealthCheckProvider provider;\n\n..........",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7565,
        "name": "Francesco Fiora",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "francesco.fiora@est.tech",
        "username": "FrancescoFioraEst"
      },
      "updated": "2021-12-13 14:41:19.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
